<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electoral Service Approves Congressional Election Results </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0902203094 Santiago EL MERCURIO in Spanish 26 Jan 94 p C3 </F>
<F P=103> PY0902203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago EL MERCURIO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The National Electoral Service (Tricel) has 
officially proclaimed the senators and deputies who were elected 
in the December 1993 elections. 
  The lawmakers were thus authorized to assumed their posts on 
11 March. 
  Tricel President Enrique Zurita Camps, who is also a Supreme 
Court member, delivered to the presidents of the Senate and the 
Chamber of Deputies, Gabriel Valdes and Jorge Molina, 
respectively, the official document with the proclamation of the 
citizens who were elected congressmen. 
  Zurita Camps reported that neither of the two appeals filed 
on the election of senators or any of the 42 appeals filed on 
the election of deputies were granted. Consequently, the figures 
released by the Interior Ministry after the elections have not 
been substantially changed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

