  [Text] Two witnesses in the U.S. Embassy bodyguard's case 
will reportedly testify on Wednesday at the 1st Court in 
Sensuntepeque. According to judicial sources, the witnesses had 
already testified but their version of the incident is 
confusing. It was added that Israel Vasquez, a driver, had said 
the Salvadoran bodyguard's death occurred as a result of an 
attack by robbers. 
  National Civilian Police sources indicated U.S. Major Ismael 
Lopez shot his bodyguard and killed him, later abandoning him 
inside the vehicle. The case has caused a controversy among the 
various government agencies because the U.S. military officer 
was illegally taken out of the country to Panama. 

