<H3> <TI>   Air Force Plane Crashes; Cause Unknown </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0902125794 San Salvador Canal Doce Television in Spanish 
0300 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0902125794 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Canal Doce Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Up-to-Date" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A search has been under way since last night for a 
Salvadoran Air Force A-37 Cessna airplane with two soldiers on 
board which, according to official sources, crashed into the 
Pacific Ocean. The cause of the crash is not known yet. 
  The Armed Forces' Center for Communications and Protocol 
[Centro de Comunicaciones y Protocolo del Ejercito] disclosed 
today the pilots on board are Captain Julio Cesar Godoy and 
Technician Juan Carlos Garcia. The airplane crashed into the 
ocean near Amatecampo Beach, La Paz Department. 
  According to the official note, Navy and Air Force units 
have 
been searching for the airplane ever since the accident was 
reported. The pilots were conducting night training when the 
accident occurred. 

</TEXT>

