<H3> <TI>   Lage Arrives in Colombia; Meetings Scheduled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0902191294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0902191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Vice President Carlos Lage Davila [title as 
heard] is in Colombia, as part of a tour that included Brazil 
and Venezuela. This visit will contribute to strengthening the 
bilateral ties between Colombia and Cuba following the 
resumption, just over three months ago, of diplomatic relations 
between the two countries. 
  Today Lage will meet with Colombian President Cesar Gaviria 
and, during his official visit to Colombia, will meet with the 
ministers of foreign trade, agriculture, economic development, 
and health. 
  Before returning to our country, Lage, who is also secretary 
of the executive committee of the Council of Ministers, will 
meet with the board of directors of the Bank of the Republic, 
which sets and regulates the nation's financial and fiscal 
policy. 
  Tomorrow, invited by the powerful National Association of 
Industrialists, Lage Davila will attend a working breakfast with 
representatives of that association, of exporters associations, 
of financial institutions, and of small and medium-sized 
industries, among others. 

