<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aristide Spokesman on Canadian-Haitian Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0902193394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0902193394 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The week of solidarity with the Haitian people began 
on 8 February. On this occasion, President Aristide's spokesman 
Jean-Claude Martineau spoke extensively on the planned 
cooperation between the Canadian Government and the Haitian 
Government during a speech on the Haitian crisis. Mr. Martineau 
explained that the Aristide government will conclude once again 
an agreement with the Hydro-Quebec International Company for the 
renovation of the drinking water and electric energy 
distribution systems. Within the scope of this week of 
solidarity, several major Haitian and U.S. [as heard] figures 
will call on the Clinton government on 10 February to support 
the proposal on strengthening sanctions against Haiti. 

</TEXT>

