<F P=100> INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Banana Producers Unable To Form Bloc for New Accord With EC </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0702190394 Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA in Spanish 6 Feb 
94 p 8D </F>

<F P=103> PA0702190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL PANAMA AMERICA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Carlos Anel Cordero and Arnulfo Barroso Watson] </F>
  [Text] Latin American banana producers so far have been 
unable to form a bloc to make a specific proposal to the EC 
regarding negotiations for a new agreement on banana exports to 
Europe. 
  Enrique Bethancour, executive director of the Union of 
Banana-Exporting Countries (Upeb), said yesterday 
representatives of Upeb countries have decided to undertake the 
negotiations with the Europeans collectively and within the 
framework of GATT rules. 
  Not all representatives of the countries that are members of 
this organization have agreed with this proposal, however. 
  During the 5 February meeting in Panama City, it was decided 
to invite Colombia, Costa Rica, Venezuela, and Nicaragua, which 
to date have not accepted the proposal by the majority of Upeb 
members. 
  Panama, Guatemala, and other producers, including Ecuador, 
the world's largest producer and not a Upeb member, maintain the 
negotiations must be held within the free trade framework 
established by GATT. 
  Ricardo Fabrega, Panamanian commerce and industries 
minister, 
said on 4 February the proposal that would be analyzed in this 
meeting consisted of a specific quota, which he refused to 
disclose, and two tariff levels. He said the first tariff level 
would be established at 7 percent. There would be a second 
tariff level after the requested quota is filled, and this level 
would be reduced in the next seven years. 
  Fabrega added the quota to be requested from the European 
Union would include the quantities sold to the Nordic countries 
and Austria, which will become EC members in 1995. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-32604 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat028_b_94008" </HT>


