in Spanish 1300 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0902165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Government Secretary Jorge Carpizo granted an 
interview during which he spoke about an agreement for peace, 
democracy, and justice signed by eight political parties. He 
said the agreement signed by eight of the nine registered 
political parties to contribute to the peace process and honest 
elections in 1994 is well on its way to fulfillment. 
  [Begin Carpizo recording] No party will issue reports on its 
own. News and reports will be issued jointly. [end recording] 
  He said that the gentlemen's agreement between leaders and 
presidential candidates is intended to protect and consolidate 
the peace agreement. Carpizo added that special congressional 
sessions can be held to reform the Federal Code of Electoral 
Institutions and Procedures if there is a consensus among the 
parties to do so. 
  Carpizo was interviewed after a meeting at the government 
secretariat with leaders of the National Teachers' Union headed 
by Elba Esther Gordillo. 

