<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economy Minister on Increasing Trade With Iran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0902152894 Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO in Spanish 4 
Feb 94 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> PY0902152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There are good prospects that Uruguay will increase 
its exports to Iran. This statement was made by Economy 
Minister Ignacio de Posadas yesterday upon his return from Iran 
where he headed a commercial mission. 
  De Posadas, who refrained from discussing domestic economic 
policy, told television Channel 10 that Iranian authorities and 
businessmen welcomed the initiative to resume the exchange of 
products, such as meat, where Uruguay has lost its privileged 
position in the Iranian market. 
  De Posadas explained: "There is interest in establishing a 
payment mechanism to safeguard the two parties, which was one of 
the important subjects discussed." 
  Regarding the products that may be of greater interest in 
the 
Iranian market, he mentioned rice, beef, milk by-products, and 
textiles. 

</TEXT>

