<H3> <TI>   New Air Force Chief Assumes Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0902151694 Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO in Spanish 2 
Feb 94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PY0902151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo EL OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Quotation marks as published] </F>
  [Excerpt] Assuming his new post on 1 February, Lieutenant 
General (Air Force) Raul Sampedro, the new commander in chief of 
the Air Force, urged his subordinates to "strictly obey, without 
exception, the constitutional precept that bans them from any 
public or private act of a political nature -- with the 
exception of the act of voting." 
  The Armed Forces, and thus the Air Force, are traditionally 
one of the basic guarantors of the electoral process, giving the 
citizens the necessary security to vote freely," he said. He 
added: "This is the way it is and this is the way it will be." 
  He stated: "An essential condition for this is the fact that 
all military personnel on active service in the Air Force, from 
the commander in chief to the lowliest soldier, must strictly 
obey without exception this constitutional concept." [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

