<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0902190994 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0902190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sandra Vergara from the "National Newscast] </F>
  [Text] Defense Minister [Rafael Pardo] has joined 
President Cesar Gaviria at the center of the scandal over the 
presence of U.S. troops in Colombia because Pardo signed an 
agreement without first advising the president. The minister is 
currently in Juanchaco inspecting the controversial projects 
with some congressmen. 
  [Begin recording] [Vergara] How do you feel about the 
upcoming political trial against you and the president? 
  [Pardo] I have absolutely no doubts; no legal or political 
doubts. There is nothing dishonorable about this, nothing I 
would term as a mistake. Our actions have always been based on 
a legal interpretation that we consider correct, and also on 
factors of convenience that we consider important. 
  [Vergara] Did the president know about this agreement? It 
has been said that he did not know about it; that his signature 
appears on the document but that he knew nothing about it. 
  [Pardo] The president is aware of how these agreements are 
established. He is aware of how military cooperation procedures 
are handled. The president was not consulted about the content 
of this memorandum of understanding because that would have been 
a deviation from normal procedures. This is directly under the 
jurisdiction of the Defense Ministry. [end recording] 
  [Vergara] Minister Pardo and the congressional Foreign 
Relations Committee are inspecting Juanchaco to determine what 
projects are actually taking place in that region. 

</TEXT>

