<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pedro Ross Addresses Villa Clara CTC Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1002203894 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1002203894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] During a meeting at which the Villa Clara Province 
CTC [Cuban Workers Federation] presented its progress report to 
the CTC national secretariat, Pedro Ross stated that the 
performance of Villa Clara Province workers was satisfactory in 
1993, but that more emphasis must be placed on the development 
of programs essential to the nation, such as the sugarcane/sugar 
program, the tobacco program, and others that affect the 
population's nutrition. Here is journalist Benito Cuadrado with 
more information. 
  [Cuadrado -- live by phone or recorded] The CTC's secretary 
general pointed out that Villa Clara's union activities are 
exemplary, but that decreases in production such as those 
exhibited on the tobacco plantations in (Manicaragua) and in the 
fishing sector must be avoided because the nation needs those 
resources to increase its economic potential. 
  The CTC national secretariat expressed interest in the 
sugarcane harvest strategy in Villa Clara; the cane planting, 
which will exceed 170 caballerias this month; and the progress 
of the potato campaign. The goal is to obtain over 6,000 
quintals of yield. 
  Ross Leal, who is a member of the Politburo, said that those 
who accomplish their respective missions must be acknowledged 
and encouraged because these times call for labor feats, and the 
people of Villa Clara always walk that path. 

</TEXT>

