<H3> <TI>   Lage, Gaviria Discuss Fuel Purchases, Medicine Exports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1002175094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1331 
GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1002175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Carlos Lage, vice president of the executive 
committee of the Council of Ministers [title as heard], says he 
encountered a very firm position on the part of the presidents 
of Brazil, Venezuela, and Colombia against the economic, 
financial, and trade blockade imposed on Cuba by the United 
States. 
  Regarding his talks with Colombian President Cesar Gaviria 
yesterday, Lage stressed that they were on increasing trade 
relations through increasing fuel purchases by Cuba directly 
from Colombia, and on exporting Cuban medicines to Colombia. 

