<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Regrets Murder of Colombian Ambassador </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1002191494 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1824 GMT 10 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1002191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tegucigalpa, 10 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- The Honduran 
Government today expressed regret over the death of Colombian 
Ambassador to Honduras Lucelly Garcia de Montoya, who was 
murdered by unidentified individuals early today near Ibague, 
Colombia. 
  Honduran Foreign Minister Ernesto Paz Aguilar said that his 
country's government sent "its most sincere condolences" in the 
wake of the diplomat's murder. This incident "reflects the 
dramatic situation facing the Colombian nation, but we are sure 
they will move forward," he added. 
  Garcia de Montoya, 60, accompanied Colombian President Cesar 
Gaviria Trujillo to the inaugural of new Honduran President 
Carlos Roberto Reina on 27 January in Tegucigalpa. 
  The foreign minister said that the Honduran president had 
already contacted his Colombian counterpart to condemn the 
incident and convey the condolences of the Honduran people and 
government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

