<F P=100> Bolivia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aranibar Notes Willingness To Approach Mercosur </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1202155394 La Paz Radio Fides Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1202155394 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Radio Fides Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bolivian Foreign Minister Antonio Aranibar pointed 
out yesterday in the capital of the Oriental Republic of Uruguay 
that Bolivia is willing to gradually -- and with increased 
strength -- approach the member countries of the Common Market 
of the South, Mercosur, made up of Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, 
and Uruguay. 
  Aranibar is in Montevideo, the capital of the Oriental 
Republic of Uruguay, where he is participating in a Latin 
American Integration Association, Aladi, meeting. There are 
problems regarding the participation of Mexico -- which has 
already signed an agreement with Canada and the United States -- 
as far as the free trade agreement is concerned. 

</TEXT>

