<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Reportage on Economic Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1002203294 </F>
<F P=103> PY1002203294 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Bolivia through 10 February: 
  The Andean Development Corporation, CAF, and Bolivian 
Government Oil Deposits, YPFB, signed a $20 million loan 
agreement on 28 January. This credit, which will not have to be 
secured by government collateral, is the first of its kind and 
will be earmarked for the purchase of supplies and drilling 
equipment to step up production. (La Paz Television Boliviana 
Network in Spanish 1700 GMT 28 Jan 94) 
  National Statistics Institute Director Luis C. Jemio 
Mollinedo reported that the January inflation rate was 0.83 
percent, the lowest rate in the past few years. The cumulative 
inflation rate was 9.53 percent in 1993. (La Paz HOY in Spanish 
2 Feb 94 p 5) 

</TEXT>

