<F P=101> El Salvador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Death Squad Reportedly Murders FMLN Activist </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1002171794 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1546 GMT 10 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1002171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Salvador, 10 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- Three masked 
individuals killed a member of the Farabundo Marti National 
Liberation Front (FMLN) Political Party, the FMLN reported 
today. The FMLN activist was identified as Ismael Bernardino, 
and the incident took place early on Wednesday in the town of 
Nahuizalco, in western Sonsonate Department. 
  FMLN spokeswoman Aida Sanchez explained that according to 
preliminary reports in her possession three individuals went to 
Bernardino's home and killed him. "The hooded individuals were 
carrying large caliber weapons," the relatives of the victim 
indicated. Sanchez stated the men tried to create the 
impression this was a burglary but did not take anything from 
the house. It cannot be ruled out that a death squad killed 
Bernardino, who was fully participating in the political 
campaign, since these groups "are still active" in El Salvador, 
the spokeswoman stressed. 
  Representative of the UN Observers for El Salvador went to 
the site to begin an investigation. 

</TEXT>

