<H3> <TI>   Memorandum, Agreement Signed With Portugal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1002181694 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 0900 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1002181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by (Arlette Milhomem)] </F>
  [Text] Brazilian Foreign Minister Celso Amorim and 
Portuguese Foreign Minister Jose Durao Barroso have signed a 
memorandum of understanding whose main point involves the 
recognition of professions in the two countries. 
  The recognition of diplomas will be studied by the 
professional associations of the two countries. If no agreement 
is reached, the governments intend to draft specific legislation 
that will ensure the validity of registries. 
  Minister Celso Amorim noted that it will now be up to the 
Portuguese institutions to discuss the situation of these 
professionals. He noted that the agreement applies to 
professions such as attorneys-at-law, doctors, and architects. 
  The two ministers also signed an agreement that guarantees 
the promotion and protection of investments between the 
governments of Brazil and Portugal. 
  Foreign Minister Durao Barroso believes that this also 
represents a great opening for Brazil to negotiate with other 
European nations. 

</TEXT>

