<H3> <TI>   President Pardons Soldiers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1302012794 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1302012794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Cecilia Pachano from "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President of the Republic Rafael Caldera has signed 
orders to release the 23 military officers and soldiers who 
participated in the 4 October and 27 November 1992 coups. 
  Of the total number, 18 soldiers were involved in the 27 
November coup, while the other five participated in the 4 
October attempt. Both coups took place during the administration 
of former President Carlos Andres Perez. 
  The presidential pardon ensures the release of Army 
Lieutenant Colonel Raul Henriquez Salmeron, retired Army Lt. 
Col. Miguel Armando Madrid Bustamante, retired Frigate Lt. (Arne 
Stevenson Chacones Escamillo), National Police Major Carlos 
Jesus Salima Colina, Air Force Maj. Jose Rafael Azuna Olivieri, 
Air Force Sergeant Tony Arenas Cordero, Air Technician Rigoberto 
Serrano Sanchez, Army Captain Carlos Guillen Celis, Capt. 
Joaquin Suarez, Sgt. (Ivan Alexander Fleiter Rosales), Raul 
Antonio Valera Marin, Jesus Maria Lopez, Juan Ramon Mena 
Soriano, Angel Didio Lobo, Wilfredo Aguilera Orellana, Hermes 
Rafael Cabello Rodriguez, Antonio Julian Lestre, Juan Ubaldo 
Balladares Padilla, Moises Daniel Flores, Antonio Cubides 
Subero, (Juan Carlos Herrerabalbuena), Jorge Alonso Flores, and 
Eduardo Jose Garrido Martinez. 

</TEXT>

