<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Cease-Fire' Continues To Hold </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1102194894 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1102194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The cease-fire agreed upon by the Sandinist People's 
Army [EPS] and the anti-Sandinist rebels in northern Nicaragua 
is being kept, a military spokesman reported on Thursday. There 
have not been any clashes between the EPS and the 3-80 Northern 
Front led by recontra leader Jose Angel Talavera, alias El 
Chacal, the military source added. 
  A peace commission traveled on Thursday to the Quilali area 
in an attempt to make contact with rebel leaders to present a 
government proposal for the pacification of the nation's 
conflict-ridden and tormented northern areas. The peace 
commission is made up of members of the Nicaraguan Catholic 
Church and of the International Commission of Support and 
Verification, CIAV-OAS. 
  On Wednesday, the Nicaraguan Government and the rebels each 
announced -- unilaterally -- a cease-fire aimed at finding a 
negotiated solution to the conflict. 

</TEXT>

