<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies Elect New Comptroller General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1202023794 Managua Radio Corporacion in Spanish 2200 GMT 
11 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1202023794 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Corporacion </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Five O'Clock Sharp" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A new comptroller general of the Republic was 
appointed today. There was no doubt; there was no reason to 
suspect otherwise. The person Presidency Minister Antonio Lacayo 
nominated, in other words, his friend Engineer Arturo Harding 
Lacayo, was appointed comptroller general of the Republic in 
elections in which the 74 deputies who attended the plenary 
session participated. 
  Harding got 57 votes and Juan Gutierrez got two votes. One 
vote was from Humberto Castilla and the other vote was from 
Humberto Hassan. Customs General Director Guillermo Ruiz also 
received two votes. There were thirteen abstentions from a total 
of 74 nominal votes, meaning each deputy's name was called and 
each one said for whom he was voting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

