<F P=102>  PA1202043694 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1202043694 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Before the Criminal Court's decision on La 
Cantuta case was known, opposition congressmen had presented an 
appeal for the protection of civil rights to the 22d Court 
asking that the controversial Law on Venue Dispute not be 
implemented. Later they visited with the president of the 
Supreme Court and asked that the Law on Venue Dispute not be 
implemented. 
  A few hours before the Supreme Court ruled on the Law on 
Venue Dispute, opposition congressmen represented by Henry 
Peace, Fernando Olivera, Robert Caceres, Manuel Moreira, and 
Antero Flores, among others, presented an appeal for the 
protection of civil rights so the law is not enforced. The 
document was received by Justice Rafael Yager in his office. The 
appeal included a precautionary measure so that the law would 
not be applied to La Cantuta case. [passage omitted] 

