<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Extends State of Emergency in Provinces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1002124494 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1002124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a supreme decree published in the 
official gazette, the government has officially extended the 
state of emergency in the provinces of Paruyo, Comayo, 
Chumbivilcas, Ascona, and Canchis in Cuzco until 19 March. 
Consequently, the constitutional guarantees related to the 
inviolability of personal domicile, the right to move freely in 
the country, and the right to hold peaceful and unarmed meetings 
remain suspended. 
  The decree dictates that such emergency measures will 
facilitate the antiterrorist operations in this part of the 
country. The Armed Forces will ensure an internal order, in 
accordance with the existing laws, in those provinces. 

</TEXT>

