<H3> <TI>   Standing Committee condemns New U.S. Immigration Measures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1002143594 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1002143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Standing Committee of the Congress of the Union 
on 9 February condemned the new immigration measures adopted by 
the U.S. Government as well as the intensification of military 
surveillance along the Mexican-U.S. border. The measures 
adopted by the U.S. Government do not solve the illegal alien 
immigration problem. 
  An agreement approved by all political parties called for, 
through the Human Rights and Border Issues Committees, public 
audiences to discuss mechanisms to promote the defense and 
protection of the rights of our fellow immigrant citizens. 

