<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Rejects U.S. Human Rights Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1002014694 Asuncion RPC Television Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1002014694 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion RPC Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] There are tensions in Paraguayan-U.S. relations. 
The Paraguayan Government today formally rejected the U.S. State 
Department report on human rights violations in our country. 
After meeting with Foreign Minister Luis Maria Ramirez 
Boettner, U.S. Ambassador Jon Glassman noted, however, that the 
report is completely objective. 
  The report, which has revealed worldwide that human rights 
continue to be violated in our country, was formally rejected by 
the government. To this end, Foreign Minister Ramirez Boettner 
summoned Ambassador Glassman. The details of the rejection have 
not been disclosed because Ramirez Boettner continues to be 
reluctant to answer reporters' questions, and Glassman, for 
diplomatic reasons, declined to elaborate on the subject. He 
displayed, however, his disagreement with our government's 
position because, in his opinion, the report is quite objective. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

