<H3> <TI>   Havana Notes DPRK Rejection of U.S. `Pressuring' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1202160294 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1506 GMT 
12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1202160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The DPRK will consider a declaration of war any kind 
of sanction promoted by the United States against the DPRK in 
order to to solve the nuclear disagreement on the peninsula. The 
daily paper RODONG SHINMUN affirms that the U.S. Government is 
exacerbating the situation by pressuring Pyongyang to accept a 
total inspection by the International Atomic Energy Agency, 
threatening to take the nuclear problem before the UN Security 
Council. 
  North Korea has repeatedly denied charges that it is 
developing nuclear weapons on its territory and rejected the 
inspection by the international agency arguing that its 
installations are devoted to peaceful ends. 
  The DPRK calls unjustified the position that has been taken 
by the White House and insists that a negotiated solution can be 
reached only through talks between Washington and Pyongyang, in 
order to reach a global agreement. 

</TEXT>

