<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Terms France Visit `Positive' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1202050194 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 0000 GMT 10 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1202050194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Evening Information Review" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Ricardo Alarcon, president of the National Assembly 
of the People's Government, has termed his meetings in France as 
very positive. France is the third country he visited as part 
of a tour of Europe, which, he said, has been very fruitful and 
has demonstrated the friendship and affection of the people of 
France for the Caribbean island. This has materialized in the 
sending of donations, he continued. 
  In statements to Radio Rebelde, Alarcon said his meeting in 
Paris with (Robert Hue), new secretary general of the French 
Communist Party, was very friendly. Alarcon said (Hue) 
reiterated his party's support for Cuba and vowed to maintain 
the solidarity movement toward the Caribbean nation. 
  Upon assessing his tour, which also included Germany and 
Belgium, the president of Cuba's legislative body added that 
there is a great and growing interest in Europe in learning 
about Cuba's reality. He stressed that the initial amazement 
over Cuba's survival without assistance from the now defunct 
Soviet Union and the socialist bloc is over. 
  Alarcon told Radio Rebelde that currently on the continent 
there is a great deal of interest in learning about the problems 
of the island, how they are being confronted, and the current 
development perspectives, because for many people in Europe this 
is a very unique case. He added that this is a country facing 
serious economic difficulties, which has continued to preserve 
firm human values of respecting people and maintaing a feeling 
of solidarity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

