<F P=101> Costa Rica </F>
<H3> <TI>   Niehaus Says OAS Should Hold Americas Summit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1002233694 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2219 GMT 10 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1002233694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] San Jose, 10 Feb (NOTIMEX) -- The Costa Rican 
Foreign Ministry announced today that it believes the Summit of 
the Americas proposed by the United States should be held by the 
OAS. [passage omitted] 
  Costa Rican Foreign Minister Bernd Niehaus stressed that 
"without a doubt the summit will be of great importance for the 
future of America, but unfortunately the OAS, which is the 
appropriate international organization to hold such a summit, 
has not been taken into consideration." 
  Niehaus held a news conference during which he added that 
"we 
consider this initiative to be very important and welcome it 
without reservation, but it would be important if the meeting 
were organized and had the logistical support of the OAS in a 
parallel manner and with the will of all countries that form 
that organization." 

</TEXT>

