<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage, Comment on La Cantuta Case, Events </TI></H3>
<H4>   Justice Minister: Military To Try Case </H4>
<F P=102> PA1402222594 Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network in 
Spanish 1800 GMT 14 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1402222594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Radio Programas del Peru Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Peruvian Justice Minister Fernando Vega Santagadea 
has told the UN Human Rights Commission in Geneva military 
courts will try the soldiers allegedly involved in the murder of 
10 people at La Cantuta University. The minister has said if 
Armed Forces members are indeed involved in this crime, their 
sentences will show there is no impunity in Peru. 
  On another topic, Vega has also reported that 95 percent of 
terrorist leaders are now in jail and that hope has been 
restored in Peru. The shadow of Marxist-Leninist-Maoist 
Communism no longer hovers over the country's future, the 
justice minister has said. He added, however, the struggle 
against terrorism and the state of emergency continued, and he 
justified the validity of several measures geared toward 
punishing and eradicating subversion. 

</TEXT>

